<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>How often does Google update its algorithm?</strong></p>
<p>Google makes thousands of small changes per year. Major confirmed updates (core updates and spam updates) happen 5-8 times per year. Core updates typically roll out 3-4 times annually. Each core update takes 1-3 weeks to complete.</p>
<p><strong>What is a Google core update?</strong></p>
<p>A core update is a broad change to how Google evaluates content quality. It does not target specific sites or techniques. Instead, it reassesses which pages best satisfy search queries. Sites can gain or lose rankings based on relative quality compared to competitors.</p>
<p><strong>How do I know if a Google update affected my site?</strong></p>
<p>Check your Google Search Console data for sudden drops in impressions and clicks. Compare the timing against Google's <a href="https://developers.google.com/search/updates/ranking">Search Status Dashboard</a>. If the drop aligns with a confirmed update date, the update likely caused it.</p>
<p><strong>How long does it take to recover from a core update?</strong></p>
<p>Most meaningful recoveries take 4-6 months. The fastest recoveries happen when the next core update reassesses improved content. There is no instant fix. Recovery requires genuine content improvements aligned with E-E-A-T principles.</p>
<p><strong>Does Google penalize AI content?</strong></p>
<p>No. Google does not penalize AI-generated content by default. It penalizes low-quality content regardless of how it was produced. AI content that lacks human expertise, editorial review, and unique value will lose rankings. AI content that includes genuine expertise and adds real value can rank well.</p>
<p><strong>What is the best way to protect against future updates?</strong></p>
<p>Publish expert-level content with verifiable authorship, original data, and genuine insights. Maintain strong technical performance. Build natural backlinks. Update content regularly. Sites that follow <a href="/blog/seo-for-beginners/">SEO best practices</a> consistently perform well through algorithm changes.</p>
<p>Google algorithm updates reward sites that genuinely help searchers. The pattern has been consistent since 2011. Every major update pushed the same direction: better content wins. Build your SEO strategy around quality, expertise, and consistency. The updates will take care of the rest.</p>
